{"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PtrArrayRef","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PtrArrayRef\/PtrArrayProtocol-Implementations"]]},"metadata":{"fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"steal","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"len","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sp","text":"UnsafeMutablePointer"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"text":"gsize","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gsize","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":">!) -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"UnsafeMutablePointer","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sp"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gpointer","text":"gpointer"},{"kind":"text","text":"?>!"}],"modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"extendedModule":"GLib","title":"steal(len:)","roleHeading":"Instance Method","symbolKind":"method","role":"symbol","externalID":"s:4GLib16PtrArrayProtocolPAAE5steal3lenSpySvSgGSgSpySuGSg_tF::SYNTHESIZED::s:4GLib11PtrArrayRefV"},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PtrArrayRef\/steal(len:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/ptrarrayref\/steal(len:)"]}],"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Frees the data in the array and resets the size to zero, while","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the underlying array is preserved for use elsewhere and returned"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"to the caller."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"steal","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"len","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sp","text":"UnsafeMutablePointer"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"text":"gsize","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gsize"},{"text":">! = nil) -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"UnsafeMutablePointer","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sp"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"gpointer","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gpointer"},{"kind":"text","text":"?>!"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that if the array is "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"NULL"},{"type":"text","text":" terminated this may still return"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"NULL","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" if the length of the array was zero and pdata was not yet"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"allocated."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Even if set, the [callback"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DestroyNotify","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":"] function will never be called","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"on the current contents of the array and the caller is","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"responsible for freeing the array elements.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"An example of use:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"c","type":"codeListing","code":["`g_autoptr(GPtrArray)` chunk_buffer = g_ptr_array_new_with_free_func (g_bytes_unref);","","\/\/ Some part of your application appends a number of chunks to the pointer array.","g_ptr_array_add (chunk_buffer, g_bytes_new_static (\"hello\", 5));","g_ptr_array_add (chunk_buffer, g_bytes_new_static (\"world\", 5));","","…","","\/\/ Periodically, the chunks need to be sent as an array-and-length to some","\/\/ other part of the program.","GBytes **chunks;","gsize n_chunks;","","chunks = g_ptr_array_steal (chunk_buffer, &n_chunks);","for (gsize i = 0; i < n_chunks; i++)","  {","    \/\/ Do something with each chunk here, and then free them, since","    \/\/ `g_ptr_array_steal()` transfers ownership of all the elements and the","    \/\/ array to the caller.","    …","","    g_bytes_unref (chunks[i]);","  }","","g_free (chunks);","","\/\/ After calling `g_ptr_array_steal()`, the pointer array can be reused for the","\/\/ next set of chunks.","g_assert (chunk_buffer->len == 0);"]}],"kind":"content"}],"sections":[],"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","title":"GLib","kind":"symbol","role":"collection","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glib","abstract":[]},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/PtrArrayRef":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"PtrArrayRef","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"PtrArrayRef"}],"role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/ptrarrayref","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PtrArrayRef","title":"PtrArrayRef","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Contains the public fields of a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GPtrArray"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/DestroyNotify":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Specifies the type of function which is called when a data element"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"is destroyed. It is passed the pointer to the data element and"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"should free any memory and resources allocated for it."}],"title":"DestroyNotify","fragments":[{"text":"typealias","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"DestroyNotify","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/destroynotify","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"DestroyNotify","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DestroyNotify